@page "/privacy"
@layout MainLayout

<PageTitle>Privacy Policy</PageTitle>

<div class="privacy-content">
    <h2>Privacy Policy</h2>
    <FluentDivider/>

    <nav class="privacy-toc">
        <ul>
            <li><a href="#@IntroId">Introduction</a></li>
            <li><a href="#@WhatICollectId">What I Collect</a></li>
        </ul>
    </nav>

    <h3 id="@IntroId">Introduction</h3>
    <p>
        The Shuttle web application was designed with the goal to collect as little personal information as possible
        because I do not <em>want</em> to collect it. This is a personal project and I have no desire to collect or
        monetize user data.

        It's also a royal pain in the butt to protect user data, so the less I have, the better. That being said, there are some things I have to collect
        to make the app work, so this policy outlines what I collect, why I collect it, and how I protect it.
    </p>

    <h3 id="@WhatICollectId">What I Collect</h3>
</div>